This is most likely the real 'Baratani Hill', at coordinates: -25.003473489537402, 25.73860682854558. The local name is 'Lentswe la Baratani', or 'Lover's Hill'. There is an old lore about this hill which resulted in Botswanians seeing this as a place to be left alone - basically they see the hill as being haunted by two lovers gone lost there. Other versions include a giant snake. Out of respect for the local population you may choose not to climb this hill - it is also not the highest of the area.

Google maps places 'Baratani Hill' at this location on the map, coordinates: -25.013998829785677, 25.725903543886922. This is evidently wrong as this location is not even a hilltop. The real Baratani Hill is most likely at: -25.003473489537402, 25.73860682854558 - and at that location I made a note too.
This is where google maps places 'Otse Hill' - but this is not the highpoint of the area.
